label: Behavior (IRI)
rdfs_comment: A description of the behavior shown by the subject at the time the dwc:Occurrence was recorded.
dcterms_description: Recommended best practice is to use a controlled vocabulary. Terms in the dwciri: namespace are intended to be used in RDF with non-literal objects.

label: Caste (IRI)
rdfs_comment: Categorisation of individuals for eusocial species (including some mammals and arthropods).
dcterms_description: Recommended best practice is to use a controlled vocabulary that aligns best with the dwc:Taxon. Terms in the dwciri: namespace are intended to be used in RDF with non-literal objects.

label: Data Generalizations (IRI)
rdfs_comment: Actions taken to make the shared data less specific or complete than in its original form. Suggests that alternative data of higher quality may be available on request.
dcterms_description: Terms in the dwciri: namespace are intended to be used in RDF with non-literal objects.

label: Degree of Establishment (IRI)
rdfs_comment: The degree to which a dwc:Organism survives, reproduces, and expands its range at the given place and time.
dcterms_description: Recommended best practice is to use IRIs from the controlled vocabulary designated for use with this term, listed at http://rs.tdwg.org/dwc/doc/doe/. For details, refer to https://doi.org/10.3897/biss.3.38084 . Terms in the dwciri: namespace are intended to be used in RDF with non-literal objects.

label: Disposition (IRI)
rdfs_comment: The current state of a specimen with respect to the collection identified in dwc:collectionCode or dwc:collectionID.
dcterms_description: Recommended best practice is to use a controlled vocabulary. Terms in the dwciri: namespace are intended to be used in RDF with non-literal objects.

label: Establishment Means (IRI)
rdfs_comment: Statement about whether a dwc:Organism has been introduced to a given place and time through the direct or indirect activity of modern humans.
dcterms_description: Recommended best practice is to use IRIs from the controlled vocabulary designated for use with this term, listed at http://rs.tdwg.org/dwc/doc/em/. For details, refer to https://doi.org/10.3897/biss.3.38084 . Terms in the dwciri: namespace are intended to be used in RDF with non-literal objects.

label: Event Type (IRI)
rdfs_comment: The nature of the dwc:Event.
dcterms_description: Recommended best practice is to use a controlled vocabulary. Regardless of the dwc:eventType, the interval of the dwc:Event can be captured in dwc:eventDate. Terms in the dwciri: namespace are intended to be used in RDF with non-literal objects.

label: Footprint WKT (IRI)
rdfs_comment: A Well-Known Text (WKT) representation of the shape (footprint, geometry) that defines the dcterms:Location. A dcterms:Location may have both a point-radius representation (see dwc:decimalLatitude) and a footprint representation, and they may differ from each other.
dcterms_description: Terms in the dwciri: namespace are intended to be used in RDF with non-literal objects.

label: Funding Attribution (IRI)
rdfs_comment: An organization or agency that provided funding for a project.
dcterms_description: Terms in the dwciri: namespace are intended to be used in RDF with non-literal objects.

label: Georeferenced By (IRI)
rdfs_comment: A person, group, or organization who determined the georeference (spatial representation) for the dcterms:Location.
dcterms_description: Terms in the dwciri: namespace are intended to be used in RDF with non-literal objects.

label: Georeference Protocol (IRI)
rdfs_comment: A description or reference to the methods used to determine the spatial footprint, coordinates, and uncertainties.
dcterms_description: Terms in the dwciri: namespace are intended to be used in RDF with non-literal objects.

label: Georeference Sources (IRI)
rdfs_comment: A map, gazetteer, or other resource used to georeference the dcterms:Location.
dcterms_description: Terms in the dwciri: namespace are intended to be used in RDF with non-literal objects.

label: Georeference Verification Status (IRI)
rdfs_comment: A categorical description of the extent to which the georeference has been verified to represent the best possible spatial description for the dcterms:Location of the dwc:Occurrence.
dcterms_description: Recommended best practice is to use a controlled vocabulary. Terms in the dwciri: namespace are intended to be used in RDF with non-literal objects.

label: Habitat (IRI)
rdfs_comment: A category or description of the habitat in which the dwc:Event occurred.
dcterms_description: Terms in the dwciri: namespace are intended to be used in RDF with non-literal objects.

label: Identification Qualifier (IRI)
rdfs_comment: A controlled value to express the determiner's doubts about the dwc:Identification.
dcterms_description: Terms in the dwciri: namespace are intended to be used in RDF with non-literal objects.

label: Identification Verification Status (IRI)
rdfs_comment: A categorical indicator of the extent to which the taxonomic identification has been verified to be correct.
dcterms_description: Terms in the dwciri: namespace are intended to be used in RDF with non-literal objects. Recommended best practice is to use a controlled vocabulary such as that used in HISPID and ABCD.

label: Identified By (IRI)
rdfs_comment: A person, group, or organization who assigned the dwc:Taxon to the subject.
dcterms_description: When used in the context of an Event (such as in the Humboldt Extension), the subject consists of all of the dwc:Organisms related to the Event. Terms in the dwciri: namespace are intended to be used in RDF with non-literal objects.

label: Information Withheld (IRI)
rdfs_comment: Additional information that exists, but that has not been shared in the given record.
dcterms_description: Terms in the dwciri: namespace are intended to be used in RDF with non-literal objects.

label: Life Stage (IRI)
rdfs_comment: The age class or life stage of the dwc:Organism(s) at the time the dwc:Occurrence was recorded.
dcterms_description: Recommended best practice is to use a controlled vocabulary. Terms in the dwciri: namespace are intended to be used in RDF with non-literal objects.

label: Location According To (IRI)
rdfs_comment: Information about the source of this dcterms:Location information. Could be a publication (gazetteer), institution, or team of individuals.
dcterms_description: Terms in the dwciri: namespace are intended to be used in RDF with non-literal objects.

label: Measurement Determined By (IRI)
rdfs_comment: A person, group, or organization who determined the value of the dwc:MeasurementOrFact.
dcterms_description: Terms in the dwciri: namespace are intended to be used in RDF with non-literal objects.

label: Measurement Method (IRI)
rdfs_comment: The method or protocol used to determine the measurement, fact, characteristic, or assertion.
dcterms_description: Terms in the dwciri: namespace are intended to be used in RDF with non-literal objects.

label: Measurement Type (IRI)
rdfs_comment: The nature of the measurement, fact, characteristic, or assertion.
dcterms_description: Recommended best practice is to use a controlled vocabulary. Terms in the dwciri: namespace are intended to be used in RDF with non-literal objects.

label: Measurement Value (IRI)
rdfs_comment: The value of the measurement, fact, characteristic, or assertion.
dcterms_description: Terms in the dwciri: namespace are intended to be used in RDF with non-literal objects.

label: Occurrence Status (IRI)
rdfs_comment: A statement about the presence or absence of a dwc:Taxon at a dcterms:Location.
dcterms_description: Recommended best practice is to use a controlled vocabulary. Terms in the dwciri: namespace are intended to be used in RDF with non-literal objects.

label: Pathway (IRI)
rdfs_comment: The process by which a dwc:Organism came to be in a given place at a given time.
dcterms_description: Recommended best practice is to use IRIs from the controlled vocabulary designated for use with this term, listed at http://rs.tdwg.org/dwc/doc/pw/. For details, refer to https://doi.org/10.3897/biss.3.38084 . Terms in the dwciri: namespace are intended to be used in RDF with non-literal objects.

label: Preparations (IRI)
rdfs_comment: A preparation or preservation method for a specimen.
dcterms_description: Terms in the dwciri: namespace are intended to be used in RDF with non-literal objects.

label: Recorded By (IRI)
rdfs_comment: A person, group, or organization responsible for recording the original dwc:Occurrence.
dcterms_description: Terms in the dwciri: namespace are intended to be used in RDF with non-literal objects.

label: Reproductive Condition (IRI)
rdfs_comment: The reproductive condition of the biological individual(s) represented in the dwc:Occurrence.
dcterms_description: Recommended best practice is to use a controlled vocabulary. Terms in the dwciri: namespace are intended to be used in RDF with non-literal objects.

label: Sampling Size Unit (IRI)
rdfs_comment: The unit of measurement of the size (time duration, length, area, or volume) of a sample in a sampling dwc:Event.
dcterms_description: A dwciri:sampleSizeUnit must have a corresponding dwc:sampleSizeValue. Recommended best practice is to use a controlled vocabulary such as the Ontology of Units of Measure http://www.wurvoc.org/vocabularies/om-1.8/ of SI units, derived units, or other non-SI units accepted for use within the SI.

label: Sex (IRI)
rdfs_comment: The sex of the biological individual(s) represented in the dwc:Occurrence.
dcterms_description: Recommended best practice is to use a controlled vocabulary. Terms in the dwciri: namespace are intended to be used in RDF with non-literal objects.

label: Type Status (IRI)
rdfs_comment: A nomenclatural type (type status, typified scientific name, publication) applied to the subject.
dcterms_description: Terms in the dwciri: namespace are intended to be used in RDF with non-literal objects.

label: Verbatim Coordinate System (IRI)
rdfs_comment: The spatial coordinate system for the dwc:verbatimLatitude and dwc:verbatimLongitude or the dwc:verbatimCoordinates of the dcterms:Location.
dcterms_description: Recommended best practice is to use a controlled vocabulary. Terms in the dwciri: namespace are intended to be used in RDF with non-literal objects.

label: Vertical Datum (IRI)
rdfs_comment: The vertical datum used as the reference upon which the values in the elevation terms are based.
dcterms_description: Recommended best practice is to use a controlled vocabulary. Terms in the dwciri: namespace are intended to be used in RDF with non-literal objects.

label: Vitality (IRI)
rdfs_comment: An indication of whether a dwc:Organism was alive or dead at the time of collection or observation.
dcterms_description: Recommended best practice is to use a controlled vocabulary. Intended to be used with records having a dwc:basisOfRecord of `PreservedSpecimen`, `MaterialEntity`, `MaterialSample`, or `HumanObservation`. Terms in the dwciri: namespace are intended to be used in RDF with non-literal objects.
